<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<article>
    <title>Introduction to Multimedia Content</title>

    <section id="1">
        <paragraph>
            Multimedia applications combine
            <bold>images</bold>,
            <italic>videos</italic>,
            audio, and text into a single experience.
        </paragraph>

        <paragraph>
            Images are commonly used to visually explain ideas and improve user engagement.
        </paragraph>

        <image>
            <url>https://multimedia-app-4cw7.onrender.com/images/69e05bdfc4002edfe8484133</url>
            <caption>Sample image 1 from the multimedia server</caption>
            <alt>Demo image 1</alt>
        </image>

        <image>
            <url>https://multimedia-app-4cw7.onrender.com/images/69e05be8c4002edfe8484135</url>
            <caption>Sample image 2 from the multimedia server</caption>
            <alt>Demo image 2</alt>
        </image>

        <paragraph>
            This paragraph contains a <bold>bold text</bold>, an
            <italic>italic text</italic>, and a
            <link url="https://multimedia-app-4cw7.onrender.com">server homepage link</link>.
        </paragraph>
    </section>

    <section id="2">
        <paragraph>
            Videos are useful for tutorials, demonstrations, and storytelling.
        </paragraph>

        <video>
            <url>https://multimedia-app-4cw7.onrender.com/videos/69e05c7ac4002edfe848413b</url>
            <caption>Sample MP4 video from the multimedia server</caption>
        </video>

        <video>
            <url>https://multimedia-app-4cw7.onrender.com/videos/69e05c8cc4002edfe848414b</url>
            <caption>Sample MOV video from the multimedia server</caption>
        </video>

        <audio>
            <url>https://multimedia-app-4cw7.onrender.com/audio/69e05ddcc4002edfe8484152</url>
            <caption>Sample MP3 audio explanation</caption>
        </audio>

        <audio>
            <url>https://multimedia-app-4cw7.onrender.com/audio/69e05de3c4002edfe8484156</url>
            <caption>Second MP3 audio example</caption>
        </audio>

        <explanation>
            Audio and video can work together to create a more interactive learning experience.
        </explanation>
    </section>

    <section id="3">
        <paragraph>
            External resources such as YouTube and websites can be embedded alongside local server media.
        </paragraph>

        <youtube>
            <url>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4vQ9QkRLKd0</url>
            <title>Sample YouTube Multimedia Video</title>
        </youtube>

        <website>
            <url>https://multimedia-app-4cw7.onrender.com</url>
            <title>Multimedia App Server</title>
        </website>

        <paragraph>
            You can use this XML structure in frontend applications to dynamically render
            <bold>text</bold>,
            <italic>media</italic>,
            links, and embedded content.
        </paragraph>
    </section>
</article>